  "prompt": "What is the salary of an assistant professor with a PhD in India?",
  "response": "The salary of an assistant professor with a PhD in India can vary significantly depending on the institution, location, and level of experience. As of recent trends in 2023, here are some general estimates:\n\n1. **Government Institutions**: In central government institutions such as Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) or National Institutes of Technology (NITs), the salary can range from INR 70,000 to INR 1,20,000 per month for entry-level assistant professors, including allowances like Dearness Allowance (DA), House Rent Allowance (HRA), and others.\n\n2. **State Government Colleges and Universities**: The salary here is often slightly less than central government institutions, usually ranging from INR 60,000 to INR 1,00,000 per month.\n\n3. **Private Institutions**: The salary in private colleges and universities can widely vary. Entry-level assistant professors can expect salaries ranging from INR 30,000 to INR 80,000 per month, depending on the reputation and financial health of the institution.\n\nThese figures are approximate and may vary. For the most accurate and updated information, directly checking with specific institutions or referring to official government pay scale guidelines would be advisable.",
